, pearl onions and lardons towards the end of cooking yet this states to add them along with the beef at the start and cook for the full three hours - does this make the mushrooms and lardons disintegrate? Thanks.</div></div></div></div> </article></div></div><div><div id="comment-wrapper-1049001" class="indented"><a id="comment-1049001"></a><article class="comment comment__indented-wrapper comment__indented-wrapper-1"><div class=" comment__indented comment__indented-1"> <header class="comment__header"><div class="comment__author-picture"><div class="user-picture"> <img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/avatar/public/pictures/picture-281803-1415360830.jpg?itok=HKYHujSC" width="40" height="40" alt="goodfoodteam&#039;s picture" title="goodfoodteam&#039;s picture" /></div></div><div class="comment__author-name"> <span class="username">goodfoodteam</span></div><div class="comment__date"> 19th Mar, 2018</div> </header><div class="comment__text"><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Thanks for your question. No they won't disintegrate and the flavours will permeate the sauce more.</div></div></div></div></div> </article></div></div><div><div id="comment-wrapper-846856"><a id="comment-846856"></a><article class="comment"> <header class="comment__header"><div class="comment__author-picture"> <span class="comment__author-picture--no-login"></span></div><div class="comment__author-name"> <span class="username">maggie49</span></div><div class="comment__date"> 8th Apr, 2015</div> </header><div class="comment__text"><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">I'd like to double the quantity and make it the day before. How long do you think it would take to re-heat it in the oven? Sorry to sound dim.</div></div></div></div> </article></div></div><div><div id="comment-wrap