s for the tip!</div></div></div></div></div> </article></div></div><div><div id="comment-wrapper-822111"><a id="comment-822111"></a><article class="comment"> <header class="comment__header"><div class="comment__author-picture"> <span class="comment__author-picture--no-login"></span></div><div class="comment__author-name"> <span class="username">Ani3</span></div><div class="comment__date"> 31st Dec, 2014</div> </header><div class="comment__text"><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Does the alcohol burn off while cooking or could you be over the limit if you eat it?</div></div></div></div> </article></div></div><div><div id="comment-wrapper-824241" class="indented"><a id="comment-824241"></a><article class="comment comment__indented-wrapper comment__indented-wrapper-1"><div class=" comment__indented comment__indented-1"> <header class="comment__header"><div class="comment__author-picture"><div class="user-picture"> <img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/avatar/public/pictures/picture-281803-1415360830.jpg?itok=HKYHujSC" width="40" height="40" alt="goodfoodteam&#039;s picture" title="goodfoodteam&#039;s picture" /></div></div><div class="comment__author-name"> <span class="username">goodfoodteam</span></div><div class="comment__date"> 8th Jan, 2015</div> </header><div class="comment__text"><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Hi Ani3 thanks for your question. As this dish is cooked for 3hrs with the wine it is unlikely there will be much alcoholic content in the finished dish as almost all of it will be cooked-out whilst in the oven.&nbsp;</div></div></div></div></div> </article></div></div><div><div id="comment-wrapper-821661"><a id="comment-821661"></a><article class="comment"> <header class="comment__header"><div class="comment__author-picture"> <sp